n because to its low hardness. It can clean or treat delicate substrates efficiently without producing significant damage or distortion.</li>\r\n<li>Because of its high electrical conductivity, copper cut wire shot is ideal for applications requiring electrical connection or conductivity. It is used to clean electrical contacts, connections, and other conductive surfaces in order to ensure optimal performance and resistance.</li>\r\n<li>Copper cut wire shot is favoured in non-ferrous applications where ferrous contamination must be avoided. Copper cut wire shot is used in industries such as electronics, precision equipment manufacture, and automotive to avoid ferrous particles from affecting the quality or performance of their goods.</li>\r\n<li>Copper cut wire shot can be used in ornamental finishing operations such generating a textured or polished surface on copper or other non-ferrous metals. It can aid in the creation of one-of-a-kind aesthetic effects and improve the appearance of ornamental products.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Copper Cut Wire Shot Manufacturer</h3>\r\n<p>We take pleasure in offering a great product that fulfils the different demands of our clients as a leading manufacturer of high-quality copper cut wire shot. Our copper cut wire shot is painstakingly crafted from premium-grade copper wire to provide best performance in surface treatment, cleaning, and peening applications. Our dedication to quality ensures that our copper cut wire shot consistently produces dependable and efficient results in surface treatment applications. Our copper cut wire shot is available in a variety of diameters, allowing you to choose the best shot diameter for your application. We recognise the significance of meeting our clients\' expectations and take pleasure in our ability to deliver on time, every time.</p>', 'Copper Cut Wire Shot', 'Copper Cut Wire Shot', 'Copper cut wire shot is a type of abrasive media that is used for surface treatment, cleaning, and peening.', '2023-06-02 10:38:52', '2023-06-02 10:38:52', NULL, 'admin', 'page', 'High'),
(328, 'Zinc Cut Wire Shot', 'zinc-cut-wire-shot', '45', NULL, '1687164552.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, '200 -300 /KG', NULL, NULL, NULL, '{\"name\":[\"Brand\",\"Product Name\",\"Shape\"],\"value\":[\"Spray Blast\",\"Zinc Cut Wire Shot\",\"cylindrical or spherical\"]}', '{\"name\":[\"Packaging Size\",\"Packaging SizType\"],\"value\":[\"25 kg \\/ 50 kg \\/ 1ton\",\"Wooven Gunny Bag\"]}', NULL, 'Zinc cut wire shot is a specialised abrasive medium used in a variety of industries for surface preparation, cleaning, and treatment.', '<p><strong>Zinc cut wire shot</strong> is a specialised abrasive medium used in a variety of industries for surface preparation, cleaning, and treatment. High-purity zinc wire is chopped into little cylindrical pellets or shot to make it. This one-of-a-kind non-ferrous abrasive has various distinguishing features and benefits. The non-ferrous character of zinc cut wire shot makes it perfect for applications that must avoid ferrous contamination. The usage of zinc cut wire shot can help industries such as aerospace, electronics, and sensitive equipment manufacture since it removes the chance of iron or steel particles being embedded or causing corrosion.</p>\r\n<p>Zinc cut wire shot is well-known for its toughness and durability. It is built to resist high-impact applications while still delivering efficient cleaning, surface preparation, and treatment. Because of its hardness, zinc shot may remove rust, scale, coatings, and other impurities from a variety of metal surfaces, leaving them clean and ready for further processing or finishing.</p>\r\n<p>Zinc cut wire shot is available in a variety of diameters and grades to meet the needs of certain applications. The right size or grade is determined by parameters such as the material being treated, the required impact intensity, and the desired surface quality.</p>\r\n<h2>Properties of Zinc Cut Wire Shot&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Zinc cut wire shot is a non-ferrous abrasive media, which means it contai