(335, 'Portable Sand Blasting Machine', 'portable-sand-blasting-machine', '46', NULL, '1740737185.png', 'thumb_1741006054.png', NULL, NULL, '40K-10Lakhs', NULL, NULL, '174175902316237.png', '{\"name\":[\"Product\",\"Capacity\",\"Max. Pressure\",\"Material\",\"Automation Grade\",\"Application\"],\"value\":[\"Portable Sand Blasting Machine\",\"200 Kg\",\"10000 PSI\",\"Mild Steel\",\"Semi Automatic\",\"Surface Finishing, Rust Removal\"]}', '{\"name\":[\"Brand\",\"Power\",\"Material\",\"Automation Grade\",\"Application\"],\"value\":[\"Sand Blaster\",\"3 HP\",\"Mild Steel\",\"Semi Automatic\",\"Surface finishing, Rust Removal\"]}', '<ul>\r\n<li>Surfaces can be cleaned for coating and metallization using a portable shot blasting equipment.</li>\r\n<li>Surfaces can be cleaned for coating and metallization using a portable shot blasting equipment.</li>\r\n<li>Surfaces can be cleaned for coating and metallization using a portable shot blasting equipment.</li>\r\n<li>Surfaces can be cleaned for coating and metallization using a portable shot blasting equipment.</li>\r\n</ul>', '40K-10Lakhs', '<p>A Portable Sand Blasting Machine&nbsp;can be defined as one of the effective methods with which a surface can be shaped, cleaned, and smoothened and all foreign material is removed. It can be stationary or portable in nature. Stationary Sand Blasting Machine is done in cabinets or booths whereas the&nbsp;<a href=\"#\">sand blasting hopper</a>&nbsp; can easily sandblast anything in the open area and sites.</p>\r\n<p>The material receives a completely new look and a better finish after&nbsp;sand blasting. All nooks and corners get completely clean. This method involves air blasting whereby very small material pieces are sand at very high pressure in order to etch or clean or smooth them. Surfaces are mostly mild steel, stainless steel, Aluminum, glass, stone, and wood.</p>\r\n<p>Air compressor&nbsp;for sand blasting + selected abrasive (blasting sand)&nbsp;Sand blasting hopper&nbsp;+&nbsp;<a>sand blasting nozzle</a>&nbsp;+ on/off control + blast surface = high-speed erosion (removal of dust particles from the blast surface.)</p>\r\n<h2>Portable Sand Blasting Hopper</h2>\r\n<p>A&nbsp;Sand Blasting Machine&nbsp;or portable sand blasting hopper is a machine that can be movable from one place to another easily. Sand blasting is the process of high velocity propelling a stream of blasting sand against a surface under very high pressure to smooth a rough surface, roughen a smooth surface or remove the loose particles from the metal surface. Sand used to be the most commonly used material, but since lung illness makes happens by extended inhalation of the fine dust created by sand, other materials are now used in its place. To avoid such major diseases we can use safety wears such as air blaster helmets, air conditioners, air breathers, operators&rsquo; suits, hand gloves, and gumboots.</p>\r\n<p>One thing you should never sandblast in a&nbsp;portable sand blasting machine&nbsp;other than yourself is sheet metal. This will twist regardless of pressure. The common misunderstanding is that heat is warping the sheet metal. If the blast media is harder than the metal blasted, the material is removed leaving a texture. This stretches the blasted side of metal. Use sanding methods for flat panels, or use a softer abrasive like Walnut shell or&nbsp;plastic media.</p>\r\n<h2>Specification of Portable Sand Blasting Machine</h2>\r\n<div class=\"specification-row\">\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Power</td>\r\n<td>3 HP</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Capacity</td>\r\n<td>200 Kg</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Max. Pressure</td>\r\n<td>1000 PSI</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Material</td>\r\n<td>Mild Steel</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Automation Grade</td>\r\n<td>Semi Automatic</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Application</td>\r\n<td>Surface finishing, Rust Removal</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Portable Sand Blasting Hopper</h3>\r\n<p>A&nbsp;Sand Blasting Machine&nbsp;or portable sand blasting hopper is a machine that can be movable from one place to another easily. Sand blasting is the process of high velocity propelling a stream of blasting sand against a surface under very high pressure to smooth a rough surface, roughen a smooth surface or remove the loose particles from the metal surface. Sand used to be the most commonly used material, but since lung illness makes happens by extended inhalation of the fine dust created by sand, other materials are now used in its place. To avoid such major diseases we can use safety wears such as air blaster helmets, air conditioners, air breathers, operators&rsquo; suits, hand gloves, and gumboots.</p>\r\n<p>One thing you should never sandblast in a&nbsp;portable sand blasting machine&nbsp;other than yourself is sheet metal. This will twist regardless of pressure. The common misunderstanding is that heat is warping the sheet metal. If the blast media is harder than the metal blasted, the material is removed leaving a texture. This stretches the blasted side of metal. Use sanding methods for flat panels, or use a softer abrasive like Walnut shell or&nbsp;<a href=\"#\">plastic media</a>.</p>', 'Portable Sand Blasting Machine', 'Portable Sand Blasting Machine', 'Portable Sand Blasting Machine', '2025-02-26 08:22:50', '2025-03-12 05:57:05', NULL, 'admin', 'page', 'Low');

